                            <comment id="13150556" author="tboehme" created="Tue, 15 Nov 2011 15:33:29 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;diff (against rev. 1151382 of BaseParser) of fix adding strict hexadecimal parser; the parseCOSString method could now refactored a bit to remove unnecessary hexadecimal string support&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13160959" author="lehmi" created="Thu, 1 Dec 2011 15:58:48 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I added the proposed patch in revision 1209127 with some minor changes. I also refactored the parseCOSString method.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Thaks for the controbution&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13562602" author="tchojecki" created="Fri, 25 Jan 2013 11:05:02 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I&apos;m running in some problems with this patch. We have some documents with manipulated COSStrings and the parser will run into the IOException that break the whole parsing process. I know that this are malformed document but letting the parser crash IMO isn&apos;t the best solution. Maybe returning a empty string or parsing as much bytes as possible will be a better way.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
